<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <h1>How Does Your Brain Learn?</h1>
      <p class="lead">Answer 10 short questions. Choose the option that feels most like you. At the end, we will tell which learning style suits you best: Visual, Auditory, Reading/Writing, or Kinesthetic.</p>
    </header>

    <form id="pollForm">
      <!-- Question template: each option value is V A R K -->

      <div class="q">
        <h3>1. When you study a new topic, you prefer to:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="V"> Look at diagrams, pictures, or charts</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="A"> Listen to a teacher or audio explanation</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="R"> Read notes or write summaries</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="K"> Try it myself or do a hands-on activity</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>2. To remember a new word, you usually:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="V"> Imagine a picture of the word</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="A"> Say the word out loud and listen</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="R"> Write the word several times</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="K"> Use the word in an activity or role-play</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>3. When you give directions, you:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="V"> Draw a map or point to pictures</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="A"> Explain them out loud step by step</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="R"> Give written instructions</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="K"> Walk with the person while showing the way</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>4. In class, you learn best by:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="V"> Watching demonstrations or slides</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="A"> Listening to lectures or discussions</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="R"> Reading textbooks and notes</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="K"> Doing experiments or group activities</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>5. When you try to remember a phone number, you:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="V"> Picture the numbers in your mind</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="A"> Repeat the number aloud or in your head</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="R"> Write the number down</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="K"> Dial it immediately to remember</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>6. For a new recipe, you prefer:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="V"> Looking at photos of the steps</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="A"> Listening to someone explain the recipe</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="R"> Reading the written recipe carefully</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="K"> Cooking while following the steps yourself</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>7. When you study for a test, you prefer:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q7" value="V"> Use colour notes and mind maps</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q7" value="A"> Listen to recorded lessons or talk about topics</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q7" value="R"> Make long lists and summaries</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q7" value="K"> Practice with activities and past papers</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>8. In a group project you usually:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q8" value="V"> Create the poster or slides</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q8" value="A"> Present and explain ideas aloud</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q8" value="R"> Write the report or take notes</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q8" value="K"> Build models or collect data</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>9. You prefer teachers who:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q9" value="V"> Use pictures and diagrams</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q9" value="A"> Use clear spoken explanations</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q9" value="R"> Give written handouts and notes</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q9" value="K"> Ask students to do practical tasks</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q">
        <h3>10. When you learn new grammar, you:</h3>
        <div class="options">
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q10" value="V"> Use colour-coded charts or examples</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q10" value="A"> Listen to examples and repeat them</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q10" value="R"> Read grammar rules and write exercises</label>
          <label class="option"><input type="radio" name="q10" value="K"> Use role-play or drills to practise</label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div class="controls">
          <button type="button" id="submitBtn">See My Learning Style</button>
          <button type="button" id="resetBtn" class="secondary">Reset</button>
